criteria.driver_alignment:
REPRESENT — student specified a year-by-year cash-flow model and charted free cash flows;  
IMPLEMENT — student states they automated calculations in Python and ran the model end-to-end;  
VALIDATE — student reports explicit verification checks (depreciation, terminal value, working-capital timing, sensitivity behavior).

Implemented — described automated, reproducible execution (Python) and produced outputs;  
Represent — built a detailed year-by-year cash-flow model covering EBIT, taxes, depreciation, working capital, terminal value;  
Validate — verified depreciation timing and terminal/working-capital adjustments and inspected sensitivity behavior.
